<p>&nbsp;</p>
<h2><span style="font-size:16pt"><span style="font-family:Arvo,serif">Farm Loan waiver (FLW)</span></span></h2>
<p><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="font-family:Arvo,serif">Vision mains 365_2019_7.3.2</span></span></p>
<h4><span style="font-size:12pt"><span style="font-family:Arvo,serif">Cons</span></span></h4>
<ol>
<li style="list-style-type:decimal"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="font-family:Arvo,serif">Poor economics :&nbsp;</span></span>
<ol>
<li style="list-style-type:lower-alpha"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="font-family:Arvo,serif">revenue expenditure high + high fiscal deficit + more borrowing by state =&gt; crowding out private investors</span></span></li></ol></li>
<li style="list-style-type:decimal"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="font-family:Arvo,serif">poor politics :</span></span>
<ol>
<li style="list-style-type:lower-alpha"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="font-family:Arvo,serif">Populist short term measure, political pressure on other states too, does not address the long term needs of the farmer</span></span></li></ol></li>
<li style="list-style-type:decimal"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="font-family:Arvo,serif">Sets a wrong precedent- moral hazard</span></span>
<ol>
<li style="list-style-type:lower-alpha"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="font-family:Arvo,serif">NPA defaults have increased in agricultural sector since 2016 =&gt; Honest borrowers who repay deterred</span></span></li></ol></li>
<li style="list-style-type:decimal"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="font-family:Arvo,serif"><em>Agricultural institutional credit</em></span></span><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="font-family:Arvo,serif"> access is reduced : Banks wary of giving loans to farmers =&gt; hurts marginal farmers most as he goes to informal sources of finance. </span></span><br />
<span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="font-family:Arvo,serif">Recent RBI report showed that only</span></span><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="font-family:Arvo,serif"><em><u> 40.9% of small and marginal farmers</u></em></span></span><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="font-family:Arvo,serif"> got formal loan.</span></span></li>
<li style="list-style-type:decimal"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="font-family:Arvo,serif">Since rural banks exposure is more to large farmers. The benefits will disproportionately help them.</span></span></li></ol>
<h4><span style="font-size:12pt"><span style="font-family:Arvo,serif">Pro:</span></span></h4>
<ul>
<li style="list-style-type:disc"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="font-family:Arvo,serif">Farmers are most disciplined in repayments. Only 8% rise im NPAs from agriculture&nbsp; than industry 21%.</span></span></li>
<li style="list-style-type:disc"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="font-family:Arvo,serif">Poverty and farmer suicides prevented</span></span></li>
<li style="list-style-type:disc"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="font-family:Arvo,serif">Most are small and marginal borrowers</span></span></li>
<li style="list-style-type:disc"><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="font-family:Arvo,serif">Drought year and thus government support needed</span></span></li></ul>
<h4><span style="font-size:12pt"><span style="font-family:Arvo,serif">Way forward</span></span></h4>
<p><br />
&nbsp;</p>
<h4><span style="font-size:12pt"><span style="font-family:Arvo,serif">Conclusion&nbsp;</span></span></h4>
<p><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="font-family:Arvo,serif">Instead of focussing on revenue expenditure (farm loan waiver), capital expenditure on agriculture could go a long way to augment farmer income.</span></span></p>
<p>&nbsp;</p>
<p><span style="font-size:11pt"><span style="font-family:Arvo,serif">Farm Loan waiver are a short term populist measure for long standing structural problems in agriculture. Thus a judicious use of monetary resources is called for.</span></span></p>
